      • eq

        public static PredicateIntf eq(MetafieldId inFieldId,
                               java.lang.Object inValue)
        Apply an "equal" constraint to the named property. If inValue is Null, then a isNull Predicate is returned If invalue is a Metafield, a eqProperty Predicate is returned

        Note that Hibernate will now convert a "=null" hql statement to be "is not null" under the covers. However EqPredicate preserves the ANSI-92 SQL standard for null handling so the sql matches the.

        Parameters:
        inFieldId - field id
        inValue - field value
        Returns:
        PredicateIntf

      • in

        public static PredicateIntf in(MetafieldId inFieldId,
                               java.lang.Object... inValues)
        Apply an "in" constraint to the named property

        NOTE: IN predicate expression with literals is limited to 1000 in Oracle, and in general it's not meant for a large number of items. This factory method will provide an implementation that works for large numbers, but consider using a sub query instead in this case.

        Parameters:
        inFieldId - metafield id
        inValues - field values
